description:
AMI is seeking a full time Receptionistto join the teams in the Brick office locations. This is a great opportunity to join a growing outpatient Radiology practice!


AMI offers a generous compensation package including medical, prescription, dental, vision, paid time off (PTO), Paid Holidays, 401k and Profit Sharing, among other benefits!


The Receptionist is responsible for but not limited to:

* Greeting patients and visitors promptly upon arrival, courteously, compassionately and professionally;
* Answering incoming telephone calls, makes satisfactory disposition of the calls or transfers to appropriate party;
* Maintaining surveillance of all patients and visitors in the waiting area;
* Scheduling appointments, obtaining necessary information to input computer data;
* Performing clerical functions necessary to process and maintain all records associated with the Practice, ensuring accuracy and completeness;
* Accepts responsibility and accountability for work assignments ensuring that they are completed efficiently, effectively, accurately and timely as per policy and procedure;
* At all times, maintains focus on the needs of the patient and provides high quality care and service; and
* Performs other duties as required and assigned.

This full time, 40 hour per week position is based in the Brick & Brick Women's Center offices, with a work schedule of Monday-Friday 8am-4:30pm. The schedule includes rotating Saturdays every three weeks. Schedules are subject to change based on business needs.


Candidates must have a High School Diploma or equivalent. Intermediate computer skills are required. Must demonstrate excellent customer service practicesand have the ability to work in a fast-paced environment with minimal supervision. Previous experience in a medical office or hospital is strongly preferred.Candidates must have the flexibility to work days, evenings, and weekends and rotate to other AMI office locations in the region as needed.


AMI offers a generous compensation package including medical, prescription, dental, vision, flexible spending accounts, paid time off, 401k andprofit sharing and the opportunity to work in an exciting and progressive outpatient practice.


